# Conventions

Project-specific rules. The "why" matters when judging edge cases — the rationale stays here, not in CLAUDE.md.

## File organization

{{FILE_ORG}}

<!--
  Where each kind of code goes. e.g.:
  - Reusable UI (used in 3+ places) → src/components/common/
  - Feature components → src/components/<feature>/
  - Pages (route entry points) → src/pages/
  - Pure helpers → src/utils/
  - React hooks → src/hooks/
  - Business logic with no UI → src/services/
  - Shared types → src/types/
-->

## Naming

{{NAMING}}

<!--
  - Components: PascalCase, one per file, file name = component name
  - Hooks: useCamelCase
  - Utils: camelCase
  - Types/interfaces: PascalCase, no `I` prefix
  - Test files: <Name>.test.tsx (colocated)
  - CSS classes: not applicable (Tailwind only)
-->

## Critical rules

{{CRITICAL_RULES}}

<!--
  Each rule has: the rule, the reason, the consequence if broken.
  Example:
  ### All HTTP via src/utils/api.ts
  Why: Auth headers (userId, countryCode) and error interceptor live there.
  If broken: requests miss headers; user sees "401 unauthorized" or wrong-marketplace data.

  ### Modals use createPortal to document.body
  Why: Parent overflow-hidden clips popovers otherwise.
  If broken: modal content gets clipped on dashboard pages; bug found in QA.
-->

## TypeScript / type rules

{{TYPE_RULES}}

<!--
  - No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow.
  - Component props: explicit interface, named `<Component>Props`.
  - Discriminated unions over optional flags.
  - Export shared types from src/types/, not inline.
-->

## Tooling

{{TOOLING}}

<!--
  - Lint: `npm run lint`. Fail on errors before commit.
  - Type-check: `npm run type-check` before pushing.
  - No pre-commit hooks today (note if added).
-->

